    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.18.25" />
                <fw type="curatorial">25</fw>
                
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                JOHN G. NEIHARDT
                <lb/>
                Lecturing under the Management
                <lb/>
                of
                <lb/>
                SIGURD NEIHARDT
                <lb/>
                
                
                BRANSON, MO.</fw>
                <opener><dateline>January 27, 1939</dateline>
                
                
                <address>
                <addrLine>Mr. and Mrs. Elmer E. Holm</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Mariaville, Nebraska.</addrLine>
                </address>
                
                <salute>Dear friends:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I'm sending the manuscript of "Straws". I hope you can read it at once, make your notes, and let me have it back <hi rend="underline">within two weeks</hi>. I must have some of the material for reference in preparing a week's seris of lectures before the Des Moines Forum.</p>
                
                <p>I've read the Garland brochure. Compared with yours - what a thin, perfunctory thing it is!</p>
                
                <p>Have you read Poetic Values? If not, you should I can send a copy.</p>
                
                <p>You are doing a real job. Be sure that we are sincerely grateful to you.</p>
                
                <p>I've been making astonishing progress with "Jed Smith" - 10 to 17 lines a day for some weeks! Am stopped now for some lectures; but, barring accident, I should finish in the late summer.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Kindest thoughts,</salute>
                
                <signed>Jno. G. Neihardt</signed>
                
                <signed>John G. Neihardt.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
